									<ul>
										<li><h4 style="text-align:left"><i><%= link_to "Texas Lawyer's Creed", "https://drive.google.com/file/d/1Eift2pOSMkRbYc6c76ukNPWQJ-eD1QVQ/preview", target: :_blank%></i></h4></li>
										<li><h4 style="text-align:left"><a data-toggle="modal" style="cursor: pointer;" data-target="#whyWill"><i>Why do you need a Will?</i></a></h4>

											<!-- Modal -->
											<div class="modal fade" id="whyWill" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="whyWillLabel" aria-hidden="true" style="color:black;">
											  <div class="modal-dialog" role="document">
											    <div class="modal-content">
											      <div class="modal-header">
											        <h4 class="modal-title" style="color:black;" id="whyWillLabel"><i>Why do you need a Will?</i></h4>
											      </div>
											      <div class="modal-body">
															<p>
																The general purpose for a will is to document your intentions for the disposition of your property
																after your death. And, if applicable to your situation, your will may provide for the care,
																maintenance, and support of any minor aged beneficiaries.
															</p>
															<p>
																A will provides you with a variety of benefits and advantages. The statute of descent and
																distribution (intestacy) may not match your actual intentions for the disposition of your property.
																Costs for administering an intestate estate may be significantly higher than independent
																administration as directed by you through your will. Also, your will permits you to nominate
																suitable executors and alternates. Again, if applicable to your situation, a will allows you to
																provide for and make necessary arrangements for your minor children. And for some, a will
																allows you to minimize federal and state estate tax liability.
															</p>
															<p>
																Set an appointment today.
															</p>
											      </div>
											      <div class="modal-footer">
											        <button type="button" class="button primary icon" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
											      </div>
											    </div>
											  </div>
											</div>
										<li><h4 style="text-align:left"><a target="_blank" style="cursor: pointer;" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#estateWill"><i>What are some common misconceptions for not having a Will or for failing to have an estate plan?</i></a></h4>

											<!-- Modal -->
											<div class="modal fade" id="estateWill" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="estateWillLabel" aria-hidden="true" style="color:black;">
											  <div class="modal-dialog" role="document">
											    <div class="modal-content">
											      <div class="modal-header">
											        <h4 class="modal-title" style="color:black;" id="estateWillLabel"><i>What are some common misconceptions for not having a Will or for failing to have an estate plan?</i></h4>
											      </div>
											      <div class="modal-body">
															<p>
																There are several misconceptions for not having Will or failing to have an estate plan including
																advance directives. Generally, the common misconceptions are:
															</p>
															<ul>
																<li>I do not need a Will because I have no valuable property.</li>
																<li>I do not need a Will because someone has a power of attorney for me.</li>
																<li>Probate takes years to complete and costs too much.</li>
																<li>I need a living trust.</li>
															</ul>
															<p>
																Set an appointment today and we can discuss various documents suitable for your situation.
																Professionally prepared documents can alleviate your concerns and perpetuate your desires about
																the disposition of property after your death and document your critical decisions in the event of
																you incapacity or terminal illness.
															</p>
											      </div>
											      <div class="modal-footer">
											        <button type="button" class="button primary icon" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
											      </div>
											    </div>
											  </div>
											</div>
										<li><h4 style="text-align:left"><a style="cursor: pointer;" target="_blank" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#probateAsset"><i>What are probate and non-probate assets?</i></a></h4>

											<!-- Modal -->
											<div class="modal fade" id="probateAsset" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="probateAssetLabel" aria-hidden="true" style="color:black;">
											  <div class="modal-dialog" role="document">
											    <div class="modal-content">
											      <div class="modal-header">
											        <h4 class="modal-title" style="color:black;" id="probateAssetLabel"><i>What are probate and non-probate asset?</i></h4>
											      </div>
											      <div class="modal-body">
															<p>
																When considering the disposition of your assets at death you should know what assets are
																probate assets and what are non-probate assets. Non-probate assets include:
															</p>
															<ul>
																<li>Life insurance payable to a beneficiary other than your estate.</li>
																<li>Retirement plans payable to a beneficiary other than your estate.</li>
																<li>Property held as joint tenant with right of survivorship, such as, bank accounts and
																brokerage accounts.</li>
																<li>Assets placed in trusts prior to your death.</li>
															</ul>
															<p>
																Probate assets include:
															</p>
															<ul>
																<li>Property <u>not held</u> as joint tenants with right of survivorship, such as,</li>
																	<ul>
																		<li>Real property</li>
																		<li>Stocks and bonds</li>
																		<li>Bank accounts, notes, and cash</li>
																		<li>Jointly owned property</li>
																	</ul>
																<li>Generally, personal property possessed at the time of death.</li>
															</ul>
															<p>
																Knowing the appropriate identification of your assets will assist in developing your estate plan.
															</p>
											      </div>
											      <div class="modal-footer">
											        <button type="button" class="button primary icon" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
											      </div>
											    </div>
											  </div>
											</div>
											<li><h4 style="text-align:left"><a style="cursor: pointer;" target="_blank" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#willEx"><i>What should you do with your will after execution?</i></a></h4>

												<!-- Modal -->
												<div class="modal fade" id="willEx" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="willExLabel" aria-hidden="true" style="color:black;">
